# State Management & Types

## Zustand Stores
Stores live in `store/`. The main store is `store/useAuthStore.ts` (`useUserStore`).

### Creating a New Store
```ts
// store/useExampleStore.ts
import { create } from "zustand";

interface ExampleState {
  items: Item[];
  setItems: (items: Item[]) => void;
  reset: () => void;
}

export const useExampleStore = create<ExampleState>((set) => ({
  items: [],
  setItems: (items) => set({ items }),
  reset: () => set({ items: [] }),
}));
```

Keep stores small and domain-scoped. Do not put server-fetched data in Zustand — use React Query for that.

## React Query
Use `@tanstack/react-query` for all API data fetching.

### Query Key Convention
Use descriptive array keys that mirror the API route hierarchy:
```ts
["admin", "products", page, pageSize, filters]
["admin", "orders", orderId]
["public", "news", page]
```

### Mutation Pattern
```ts
import { useMutation, useQueryClient } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { apiRoutes } from "@/lib/api/api.route";
import { toast } from "sonner";

const queryClient = useQueryClient();

const { mutate, isPending } = useMutation({
  mutationFn: (payload: CreatePayload) => apiRoutes.admin.news.createNews(payload),
  onSuccess: () => {
    toast.success("Created successfully");
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["admin", "news"] });
  },
  onError: (error: ApiError) => {
    toast.error(error.message);
  },
});
```

## TypeScript Types
Types are organised under `types/` by domain:
```
types/
  api/api-response.ts     ← ApiResponse<T> wrapper
  auth/index.ts
  admin/
    order.type.ts
    brand.type.ts
    ...
  fc/
    user.type.ts
    order.type.ts
    ...
  orders/index.ts
  customers/index.ts
  products/index.ts
```

### Rules
- Place types in the closest matching domain folder
- For admin-only types use `types/admin/`; for FC-only types use `types/fc/`
- Shared/cross-domain types go in `types/<domain>/index.ts`
- Always export both the type and any related payload/response variants:
```ts
// types/admin/news.type.ts
export interface NewsItem { ... }
export interface NewsPayload { ... }
export interface NewsResponse { ... }
export interface NewsStatus { ... }
```

## Custom Hooks
Place domain-specific hooks in `hooks/`:
- `hooks/admin/useTeam.ts`
- Follow the naming pattern `use<Domain><Feature>.ts`
- Hooks should wrap React Query calls and return `{ data, isLoading, error, mutate }`
